{"data":{"page":{"id":"e0477ab6-7aef-5ff6-a4f5-b079028835b2","html":"<p class=\"align-center\">\n<a class=\"btn\" href=\"/samples-of-work-ac457d43c60e7c96d7ff78c49c2fdcfa.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Samples of work (PDF)</a>\n<a class=\"btn\" href=\"http://work.joanmira.com/webs/slater/\" target=\"_blank\">Launch archived template</a>\n<a class=\"btn\" href=\"http://work.joanmira.com/webs/slaterusa/\" target=\"_blank\">Launch archived USA template</a>\n</p>\n<p>While I was working at Slater Labs as a software engineer, I took the creation of the company website as a side project. I wanted to explore new things, like the use of animated 3d models, playing with the webcam and the microphone and voice recognition. In a way, I wanted to mimic a little bit the kind of interactive behaviours that we were building for the desktop applications of the company.</p>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 1000px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 57.099999999999994%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"1\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/9a288d2f9693b43681f81a47a6e112b4/877ff/1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9a288d2f9693b43681f81a47a6e112b4/d2504/1.jpg 500w,\n/static/9a288d2f9693b43681f81a47a6e112b4/877ff/1.jpg 1000w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\"\n      />\n  </span></p>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 1000px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n